Click "Create new file"
Write the directory with a filename like "home/new_dir/new_dir2/.../filename"
The new folders are made as written, so new_dir is in home directory etc.
Empty folders can't be made, only making through "Create new file"

Also written in:
https://stackoverflow.com/questions/18773598/creating-folders-inside-github-com-repo-without-using-git
